03:12.560 --> 03:13.727
Luisa.

03:15.028 --> 03:17.498
Luisa, are you
coming down soon?

03:32.280 --> 03:34.548
"Kiss number 60."

03:34.582 --> 03:37.751
"The kiss upon the eyes."

03:37.785 --> 03:39.987
"The eyelid kiss
is said to produce"

03:40.020 --> 03:43.757
"A unique sensation
of an unworldly nature,"

03:43.791 --> 03:46.960
"Running from
the base of the spine
to the knees."

03:58.406 --> 03:59.507
BELLOMY: Luisa.

04:03.911 --> 04:05.746
What you been
doing up there, dear?

04:05.779 --> 04:06.980
Studying.

04:07.014 --> 04:08.749
Well, that's good.

04:11.519 --> 04:12.620
What's that for?

04:12.653 --> 04:14.288
Number 26.

04:14.322 --> 04:15.589
Kissing a parent.

04:18.559 --> 04:19.627
Where are you going?

04:19.660 --> 04:21.829
Town.

04:21.862 --> 04:23.731
Before you go,
would you do
your dad a favor

04:23.764 --> 04:26.266
And come over here a second,
let me see how this fits?

04:28.636 --> 04:31.472
I always look
like a sick turkey.

04:31.505 --> 04:32.706
Ah.

04:32.740 --> 04:33.841
(GROANS)
The neckline is too high.

04:33.874 --> 04:34.975
Be careful...

04:36.043 --> 04:38.379
Where did you get that?

04:38.412 --> 04:40.481
That's your
mother's necklace.

04:40.514 --> 04:42.916
I found it in a box of
old letters.

04:44.452 --> 04:46.687
You gave it to her,
didn't you?

04:50.391 --> 04:52.393
I can't believe you were
ever that romantic.

04:52.426 --> 04:54.027
Ha!

04:54.061 --> 04:55.696
Did you stand
outside her window

04:55.729 --> 04:57.598
And serenade her
with love songs too?

04:58.499 --> 04:59.867
Mmm.

04:59.900 --> 05:01.068
(GARGLING)

05:03.771 --> 05:05.373
I guess not.

05:05.406 --> 05:06.840
There are other things
in the world

05:06.874 --> 05:08.609
As important as
love songs, you know.

05:08.642 --> 05:09.843
Like what?

05:09.877 --> 05:12.112
Like work songs,
that's like what.

05:12.145 --> 05:15.416
Like hymns, anthems, marches.

05:15.916 --> 05:17.317
Dirges.

05:18.486 --> 05:19.787
Never mind.

05:21.755 --> 05:22.756
(SIGHS)

05:24.658 --> 05:27.060
Papa, I've got to take wing.

05:27.094 --> 05:28.762
Be careful,
it's duck season.

05:32.433 --> 05:33.701
I don't suppose your wings

05:33.734 --> 05:36.036
Are going to
carry you anywhere
near that carnival, are they?

05:36.069 --> 05:37.605
What carnival?

05:40.574 --> 05:41.842
Luisa.

05:44.578 --> 05:46.547
You look nice in the necklace.

05:50.451 --> 05:51.752
(HAMMERING)

05:53.120 --> 05:54.388
Hi, Mr. Hucklebee.

05:58.025 --> 05:59.460
(MOUTHING WORDS)

06:00.494 --> 06:01.595
Luisa?

06:03.797 --> 06:05.433
How many times,
since they moved in,

06:05.466 --> 06:08.836
Have I told you not to talk
to that idiot next door?

06:08.869 --> 06:10.237
Couple of hundred.

06:10.270 --> 06:13.407
A couple of
hundred times you told me
not to talk to his son either.

06:13.441 --> 06:15.443
Good for me.

06:15.476 --> 06:16.810
And no carnival.

06:24.952 --> 06:28.989
* I'd like to swim
In a clear blue stream

06:29.022 --> 06:32.960
* Where the water is icy cold

06:32.993 --> 06:37.465
* Then go to town
In a golden gown

06:37.498 --> 06:41.001
* And have my fortune told

06:41.034 --> 06:45.072
* Just once, just once

06:45.105 --> 06:49.176
* Just once before I am old

06:49.209 --> 06:52.846
* I'd like to be not evil

06:52.880 --> 06:57.751
* But a little worldly wise

06:57.785 --> 07:01.622
* To be the kind of
girl designed

07:01.655 --> 07:06.627
* To be kissed upon the eyes

07:07.561 --> 07:11.632
* I'd like to dance till 2:00

07:11.665 --> 07:15.035
* Or sometimes dance till dawn

07:15.068 --> 07:18.506
* Or if the band
could stand it

07:18.539 --> 07:22.743
* Just go on and on and on

07:22.776 --> 07:26.647
* Just once, just once

07:26.680 --> 07:31.218
* Before the chance is gone

07:33.053 --> 07:37.257
* I'd like to waste
a week or two

07:37.290 --> 07:41.495
* And never do a chore

07:41.529 --> 07:44.932
* To wear my hair unfastened

07:44.965 --> 07:52.873
* So it billows to the floor

07:52.906 --> 07:59.780
* To do the things
I've dreamed about

07:59.813 --> 08:03.150
* But never done before

08:03.183 --> 08:07.220
* Perhaps I'm bad
or wild or mad

08:07.254 --> 08:10.858
* With lots of grief in store

08:10.891 --> 08:14.962
* But I want much more
Than keepin' house

08:14.995 --> 08:21.869
* Much more, much more,

08:23.904 --> 08:30.878
* Much more!

08:48.061 --> 08:49.697
Where you going?

08:49.730 --> 08:52.065
Uh, got to make sure
the hogs get fed.

08:52.099 --> 08:55.903
You're all dressed up.
Got a date with one of them?

08:55.936 --> 08:58.538
I just got to go
the store first
to get the feed.

09:00.273 --> 09:02.843
All right, and pick me up
some of that cough syrup

09:02.876 --> 09:04.845
That puts me right
to sleep, will you?

09:06.246 --> 09:08.148
I got to get back to work.

09:14.387 --> 09:18.058
(EXCLAIMS)
That's one hammer
I'll never see again.

09:18.091 --> 09:19.960
BELLOMY: Oh, yes, you will.

09:22.863 --> 09:25.599
Keep your crud
on your own side!

09:25.633 --> 09:29.302
You keep your face
and your damn bricks
out of my side!

09:29.336 --> 09:31.204
Or you'll be
wearing brick earmuffs.

09:31.972 --> 09:33.006
Thief!

09:33.040 --> 09:34.174
Murderer!

09:34.207 --> 09:35.275
Lunkhead!

09:36.409 --> 09:37.945
Fuzz bucket!

09:40.280 --> 09:44.351
He's out of his
mind with love,
that son of mine.

09:44.384 --> 09:48.055
Nothing sets
the heart a flutter,
like a good old fashion feud.

09:48.088 --> 09:51.825
What do you think will happen
when they meet on that
road to the carnival?

09:52.760 --> 09:54.662
I don't know.

09:54.695 --> 09:56.664
But they'll never
suspect we planned it.

09:56.697 --> 10:00.067
That son of mine,
he's fantastic.

10:00.100 --> 10:02.936
My daughter is fantastic too.

10:02.970 --> 10:05.773
Just think if they knew
that we wanted them wed.

10:05.806 --> 10:07.340
A pre-arranged marriage?

10:07.374 --> 10:09.242
They'd rather be dead.

10:12.245 --> 10:13.814
Children.

10:13.847 --> 10:15.015
Lovers.

10:15.048 --> 10:16.183
Fantasticks.

10:17.685 --> 10:19.119
Geese.

10:19.152 --> 10:21.188
How cruel ever we are.

10:21.221 --> 10:22.756
How crafty to know

10:22.790 --> 10:25.292
To manipulate children,
you merely say

10:26.126 --> 10:27.828
No.
No.

10:27.861 --> 10:30.197
* Oh!

10:30.230 --> 10:34.101
* Dog's got to bark,
a mule's got to bray

10:34.134 --> 10:38.138
* Soldiers must fight
and preachers must pray

10:38.171 --> 10:42.309
* And children, I guess,
must get their own way

10:42.342 --> 10:45.178
* The minute that you say no

10:46.814 --> 10:50.951
* Why did the kids
pour jam on the cat?

10:50.984 --> 10:55.088
* Raspberry jam
all over the cat?

10:55.122 --> 10:58.992
* Why should the kids
do something like that

10:59.026 --> 11:01.962
* When all that
we said was no?

11:24.017 --> 11:27.955
* Why did the kids
put beans in their ears?

11:27.988 --> 11:32.025
* No one can hear
with beans in their ears

11:32.059 --> 11:35.763
* After a while
the reason appears

11:35.796 --> 11:38.365
* They did it
'cause we said no

11:40.067 --> 11:41.902
* Your daughter
brings a young man in

11:41.935 --> 11:44.171
* Says "Do you like him, Pa?"

11:44.204 --> 11:47.174
* Just tell her,
"He's a fool"

11:47.207 --> 11:51.311
* And then,
you've got a son-in-law

11:51.344 --> 11:57.885
* You've got a son-in-law!

11:57.918 --> 12:01.221
* Sure as the June
comes right after May!

12:01.254 --> 12:05.458
* Sure as the night
comes right after day!

12:05.492 --> 12:09.129
* You can be sure
the devil's to pay

12:09.162 --> 12:13.200
* The minute that you say no

12:13.233 --> 12:15.168
* No!

12:15.202 --> 12:18.005
* Make sure you never say...

12:19.106 --> 12:23.210
* No!

12:29.416 --> 12:31.184
Kids.

12:31.218 --> 12:32.886
Won't it be nice,
when our kids are married

12:32.920 --> 12:36.023
So they can drive
each other crazy,
instead of us?

12:36.056 --> 12:38.959
Right. They're nearly there.

12:38.992 --> 12:43.330
There just one thing missing
for our hero and heroine,
a climax.

12:43.363 --> 12:46.099
You watch what you say,
you are talking
about my daughter.

12:46.133 --> 12:47.801
And speaking in
theatrical terms

12:47.835 --> 12:49.502
We have to find some way
to end the feud

12:49.536 --> 12:52.205
Without them knowing
we made the whole thing up.

12:55.008 --> 12:57.845
Well, how do you
propose we do that?

12:57.878 --> 12:59.479
That's the problem.

13:01.281 --> 13:02.983
Wait a minute.

13:05.853 --> 13:06.987
You see?

13:07.020 --> 13:08.155
Whenever you got a problem

13:08.188 --> 13:10.257
The United States
Postal Service
comes to the rescue.

13:10.290 --> 13:11.424
Yeah, they run
a tight shift.

13:11.458 --> 13:13.861
Let's go, Bellomy.
Let's have a talk
with this fellow...

13:13.894 --> 13:16.296
Are you crazy?
We can't go to the carnival,
the kids will see us,

13:16.329 --> 13:18.265
They'll think
we're looking for them.

13:18.298 --> 13:19.867
Instant heat.

13:19.900 --> 13:21.869
I seem to remember
that's good for
romance. Isn't it?

13:21.902 --> 13:23.270
Uh-huh. Uh-ah!

13:23.303 --> 13:25.138
Fuel to the fire.

13:26.273 --> 13:28.175
"Specialists in
dreams come true."

13:28.208 --> 13:30.410
"Family feud settled."

13:30.443 --> 13:32.179
What are we waiting for?

13:41.288 --> 13:43.056
(PEOPLE TALKING INDISTINCTLY)

14:01.909 --> 14:03.343
(PIANO MUSIC PLAYING)

14:16.223 --> 14:19.960
Romeo, Romeo!
Wherefore art thou, Romeo?

14:21.161 --> 14:22.595
MATT: But soft.

14:22.629 --> 14:25.598
What light through
yonder window breaks?

14:25.632 --> 14:29.169
It is the east,
and Juliet is the sun.

14:29.202 --> 14:32.639
Arise, fair sun,
and kill the envious moon.

14:33.506 --> 14:35.342
What if someone sees us?

14:35.375 --> 14:37.177
Come on.

14:37.210 --> 14:38.245
Our fathers.

14:38.278 --> 14:39.646
I don't care
about our fathers.

14:39.679 --> 14:41.348
I don't care
about the wall.

14:41.381 --> 14:44.151
I don't care about
anything but you.

14:44.184 --> 14:47.620
* If we were in
Verona long ago

14:47.654 --> 14:52.993
* And just like the story,
our true love forbidden

14:53.026 --> 14:58.098
* I would study swordplay
and I'd stand
and fight them all

14:58.131 --> 15:01.368
* Anyone who would come
between us

15:03.503 --> 15:07.107
* Would have to deal with me

15:07.140 --> 15:10.978
* I'd stand and face them all

15:11.011 --> 15:13.346
* As one by one they'd fall

15:15.048 --> 15:17.017
* You'd fight them all

15:17.050 --> 15:19.252
* They'd start to fall

15:19.286 --> 15:25.392
BOTH:
* Love conquers all!

15:25.425 --> 15:27.027
* Love!
* I am love!

15:27.060 --> 15:29.029
* You are love!
* I am love!

15:29.062 --> 15:33.433
* Better far than a metaphor
can ever, ever be

15:33.466 --> 15:35.068
* Love!
* I am love!

15:35.102 --> 15:36.203
* You are love!

15:36.236 --> 15:37.304
* I am love!

15:37.337 --> 15:38.638
* My mystery...

15:38.671 --> 15:41.141
* His mystery...

15:41.174 --> 15:47.447
* Of love

15:49.082 --> 15:53.153
* You are Polaris,
the one trustworthy star

15:53.186 --> 15:55.188
* You are!
* I am!

15:55.222 --> 15:56.689
* You are!
* I am!

15:56.723 --> 16:00.627
* You are September,
A special mystery

16:00.660 --> 16:02.629
* To me!
* To he!

16:02.662 --> 16:04.531
* To me!
* To he!

16:04.564 --> 16:08.535
* You are sunlight! Moonlight!
Mountains! Valleys!

16:08.568 --> 16:11.571
* The microscopic
inside of a leaf!

16:12.505 --> 16:13.706
* My joy!

16:13.740 --> 16:14.807
* Yes, I am his joy!

16:14.841 --> 16:17.177
* My grief!
* Yes, I am his grief!

16:17.210 --> 16:19.479
* My star!
* Yes, I am his star!

16:19.512 --> 16:22.249
* My leaf!
* Yes, I am his leaf!

16:22.282 --> 16:23.516
* Oh. Love!

16:23.550 --> 16:24.517
* I am love!

16:24.551 --> 16:26.653
* You are love!
* I am love!

16:26.686 --> 16:31.558
* Better far than a metaphor
can ever, ever be

16:33.160 --> 16:34.461
* Love!

16:34.494 --> 16:36.429
* I am love!

16:36.463 --> 16:38.298
* You are love!

16:38.331 --> 16:41.734
* I am love!

16:41.768 --> 16:44.571
* My mystery

16:44.604 --> 16:48.775
* His mystery

16:49.609 --> 16:54.347
* Of love

16:54.381 --> 16:58.151
* Love

16:58.185 --> 17:01.654
* Love

17:01.688 --> 17:08.661
* Love

17:12.732 --> 17:14.601
Do you speak English?

17:14.634 --> 17:16.769
Oh, my God.
What is it?

17:16.803 --> 17:19.071
It's my father.

17:19.106 --> 17:20.140
Must be this one.

17:20.173 --> 17:21.441
MATT: My father too.

17:21.473 --> 17:22.742
They're not
supposed to be here.

17:22.775 --> 17:24.243
Neither are we.

17:26.279 --> 17:29.249
We'll meet tonight,
by the big tree.

17:29.282 --> 17:30.417
In the moonlight.

17:30.450 --> 17:31.551
In moonlight.

17:34.621 --> 17:36.823
It's a century
till moonlight.

17:39.459 --> 17:41.461
I'll never wash
this hand again.

17:48.135 --> 17:49.302
What the devil...

17:49.336 --> 17:50.337
At your service.

17:54.341 --> 17:56.243
Wait, you the famous
El Gallo?

17:56.276 --> 17:57.344
El Gallo.

17:57.377 --> 18:00.847
Oh, yeah. See, we got your
advertisement in the mail

18:00.880 --> 18:03.583
And we got ourselves
a little problem.

18:04.251 --> 18:05.385
A love problem.

18:05.418 --> 18:07.554
You two have a love problem?

18:07.587 --> 18:10.790
And you seek sympathy
from our little
band of outcasts.

18:10.823 --> 18:12.859
What would you two be willing
to do in front of an audience?

18:14.861 --> 18:16.163
No, wait a minute...

18:16.196 --> 18:17.464
We are not
talking about us.

18:17.497 --> 18:19.366
We're talking
about our kids.

18:19.399 --> 18:21.100
Who happen to be
a boy and a girl.

18:21.901 --> 18:23.470
Less challenging.
Follow me.

18:25.472 --> 18:27.907
Although we are not
yet fully prepared

18:27.940 --> 18:30.343
The official opening
of the entire carnival,

18:30.377 --> 18:32.312
I think we can proceed
with our business here.

18:32.345 --> 18:35.348
One moment,
I'll check my files.

18:35.382 --> 18:37.284
I'm sorry,
what did you say
your names were?

18:37.317 --> 18:39.252
Hucklebee.
Bellomy.

18:39.286 --> 18:42.455
I do beg your pardon,
this is "N" through "Z."

18:42.489 --> 18:44.191
Yes, there we are,
"A" through "M."
Oh!

18:44.224 --> 18:45.292
How did you do that?

18:45.325 --> 18:47.194
It wasn't easy
it took months to
set up these files.

18:47.227 --> 18:48.261
Oh my...

18:48.295 --> 18:50.330
(WHISPERING) Quiet.
I'm beginning to
get a picture.

18:51.531 --> 18:53.866
You said you had
a daughter?

18:53.900 --> 18:56.403
Yes.
I see a girl.

18:56.436 --> 18:57.604
Is her name Luisa?

18:57.637 --> 18:58.805
Is that your
daughter's name.

18:58.838 --> 19:01.408
Yes.
That's her. Oh, look.

19:01.441 --> 19:05.412
She is standing
next to a young man
who must be, who must be...

19:05.445 --> 19:07.414
Quick, before
the image fades.

19:07.447 --> 19:09.416
Matt.
That's it.

19:09.449 --> 19:11.351
You're amazing.

19:11.384 --> 19:13.353
They seem to be
happy enough.

19:13.386 --> 19:14.421
What about the feud?

19:14.454 --> 19:16.423
Of course that's there,
I said "seem."

19:16.456 --> 19:18.691
Obviously your children
are feeling
a great deal of torment.

19:18.725 --> 19:19.726
Uncanny.

19:19.759 --> 19:22.262
And you've come to me
for some kind of magic, eh?

19:22.929 --> 19:24.163
You're in luck.

19:26.699 --> 19:28.535
Ooh!

19:28.568 --> 19:32.305
Frankly, we came to you
to find out
how to end this feud.

19:32.339 --> 19:34.641
Many paths lead
to the summit.
Follow me.

19:37.510 --> 19:39.846
You know,
we kind of thought
it'd be a good idea

19:39.879 --> 19:43.650
If my mild-mannered son
was turned into
a rip-roaring hero.

19:43.683 --> 19:45.252
Really?
Well, yes, that would be

19:45.285 --> 19:46.719
The first thought of
a common rural mind.

19:46.753 --> 19:48.788
And by an amazing coincidence,
it's also mine.

19:48.821 --> 19:50.623
Ah! Boy, are we lucky.

19:50.657 --> 19:54.894
Of course to have a hero,
you must first have a villain.

19:54.927 --> 19:58.265
That makes sense. But who?

19:58.298 --> 20:02.469
Let's think, the young lady
knows both of you,
so that wouldn't work.

20:04.971 --> 20:06.673
What about you?
Me?

20:06.706 --> 20:10.443
Oh, I couldn't
do it, for free.

20:10.477 --> 20:12.712
But for a small donation
to my favorite charity...

20:13.713 --> 20:14.814
Yeah.

20:19.519 --> 20:20.587
Yeah.

20:21.721 --> 20:23.823
(BOTH CHUCKLING)

20:23.856 --> 20:26.559
Would $60 be
an insult?

20:26.593 --> 20:28.928
Yes, but I'm used to abuse.

20:28.961 --> 20:31.998
Oh, yes. I see it,
I start to
kidnap his daughter,

20:32.031 --> 20:34.301
Your son runs in to save her.
Then a battle.

20:34.334 --> 20:36.436
I allow the boy to defeat me,
your son becomes a hero,

20:36.469 --> 20:39.005
The parents relent,
the feud is over forever.

20:40.340 --> 20:41.774
She melts into his arms.

20:43.443 --> 20:45.445
How much for such a drama?

20:45.478 --> 20:47.447
That, senor, depends.

20:47.480 --> 20:49.449
Depends on what?
On what else.

20:49.482 --> 20:50.917
The quality of the rape.

20:54.754 --> 20:56.989
Rape? No!
No rape!

20:57.023 --> 20:58.791
Oh, very well then,
the abduction.

20:58.825 --> 21:01.394
The rape, the chase,
the kidnapping.

21:01.428 --> 21:04.564
Call it what you will,
from the Latin rapere.

21:04.597 --> 21:05.865
Meaning "to seize."

21:08.735 --> 21:12.405
* Abductions, abductions,
Theatrical abductions

21:12.439 --> 21:16.376
* Complete with
maidens in distress
And fabulous productions

21:17.910 --> 21:21.514
* The sort of thing you see
Upon the operatic stage

21:21.548 --> 21:24.917
* Two lovers are meeting
Their happiness is fleeting

21:24.951 --> 21:28.888
* All at once a bandit man
Is standing there repeating!

21:28.921 --> 21:30.623
* Surrender and so forth

21:30.657 --> 21:32.592
* Give us the girl!
And so forth

21:32.625 --> 21:35.862
* In short they are surrounded
by a gang of angry men

21:35.895 --> 21:39.932
* I see it, I see it
A gang of angry men

21:39.966 --> 21:45.638
* Heaven
I can assure you
this is heaven

21:45.672 --> 21:49.576
