01:07:54.738 --> 01:08:01.378
* dance

01:08:04.881 --> 01:08:06.416
(THUNDER CRACKING)

01:08:15.459 --> 01:08:16.560
I'm suddenly afraid.

01:08:16.593 --> 01:08:18.228
Of what?

01:08:18.261 --> 01:08:19.629
I don't know.

01:08:20.464 --> 01:08:21.831
Something.

01:08:21.865 --> 01:08:23.267
Maybe you should go home.

01:08:24.934 --> 01:08:28.572
All my life I've waited
for something
magical to happen.

01:08:30.174 --> 01:08:32.276
Now at last,
with you, it will.

01:08:32.309 --> 01:08:34.711
Or what if it's
all just illusions?

01:08:35.612 --> 01:08:37.613
Sleight of hand.

01:08:38.782 --> 01:08:40.317
This for example.

01:08:42.319 --> 01:08:43.787
(PEOPLE SHOUTING)

01:08:46.723 --> 01:08:48.758
The glamorous sideshows.

01:08:49.859 --> 01:08:51.295
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:08:57.801 --> 01:08:59.169
It's all scenery.

01:09:00.370 --> 01:09:01.404
Smoke

01:09:02.238 --> 01:09:03.573
And mirrors.

01:09:04.508 --> 01:09:06.176
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:09:19.555 --> 01:09:20.857
Well, what do you think now?

01:09:23.660 --> 01:09:25.395
I think you're wonderful.

01:09:27.596 --> 01:09:30.767
But don't you understand
it was only a trick?

01:09:30.800 --> 01:09:32.236
And when you're
dealing with tricks,

01:09:32.269 --> 01:09:35.305
What you see isn't
always what you get.

01:09:48.818 --> 01:09:51.220
I'm warning you to be careful.

01:09:53.323 --> 01:09:54.758
I know you are.

01:09:56.426 --> 01:09:57.894
But I trust you.

01:09:59.829 --> 01:10:02.532
I know that you'll
make it all right.

01:10:06.336 --> 01:10:07.637
Oh, very well then.

01:10:07.671 --> 01:10:10.474
You better go pack
some things so that
we can run away together.

01:10:10.507 --> 01:10:13.410
After all, you can't
run away and stay at home
at the same time.

01:10:13.443 --> 01:10:16.413
Well, who cares
if we never see this
one goat town again.

01:10:16.446 --> 01:10:17.814
We can drop by
in five or six years

01:10:17.847 --> 01:10:19.316
To see if your father
is still alive.

01:10:22.719 --> 01:10:24.421
What?
The world

01:10:25.455 --> 01:10:26.723
Is waiting.

01:10:29.593 --> 01:10:31.027
I wonder if Matt...

01:10:31.060 --> 01:10:32.329
Matt?

01:10:36.900 --> 01:10:38.468
Never mind.

01:10:41.004 --> 01:10:42.839
All right, go.

01:10:42.872 --> 01:10:45.342
Get ready.

01:10:45.375 --> 01:10:47.877
See if you can borrow
a little money
while you're about it.

01:10:53.850 --> 01:10:55.452
Kiss me first.

01:11:19.108 --> 01:11:23.747
No matter what happens,
I'll never,
ever forget that kiss.

01:11:26.049 --> 01:11:28.084
A unique sensation
of an unworldly nature

01:11:28.117 --> 01:11:30.387
Running from the base of
the spine to the knees.

01:11:32.055 --> 01:11:33.056
(LAUGHS)

01:11:42.366 --> 01:11:43.467
Wait.

01:11:45.068 --> 01:11:48.405
Give me a trinket
to pledge that
you'll come back.

01:11:49.473 --> 01:11:50.607
That necklace.

01:11:51.541 --> 01:11:52.842
It was my mother's.

01:11:52.876 --> 01:11:55.412
Good. It will
service your pledge.

01:12:06.956 --> 01:12:08.658
I will leave you
my mother's necklace

01:12:08.692 --> 01:12:10.494
Because it is
my favorite thing.

01:12:11.761 --> 01:12:13.062
Guard it.

01:12:13.096 --> 01:12:14.798
And I'll go pack.

01:12:16.400 --> 01:12:17.867
I won't be long.

01:12:22.739 --> 01:12:24.441
You're really
taking me with you?

01:12:25.809 --> 01:12:27.110
Would I lie?

01:12:43.192 --> 01:12:44.861
I won't be long.

01:12:52.602 --> 01:12:53.737
You will be here?

01:12:54.871 --> 01:12:56.139
I promise.

01:13:12.489 --> 01:13:14.390
All right, move it out.

01:13:24.934 --> 01:13:26.169
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

01:13:49.759 --> 01:13:50.860
(EXHALES SHARPLY)

01:14:01.270 --> 01:14:04.040
Ah, the prodigal son
comes out from his trip
around the world.

01:14:04.073 --> 01:14:07.744
Allow me to say,
you look much wiser
but less well groomed.

01:14:07.777 --> 01:14:08.912
Leave me alone.

01:14:08.945 --> 01:14:11.180
Fine, I'm in a bit of
a rush, anyway.

01:14:11.214 --> 01:14:12.916
Where did you get that?
Oh, this?

01:14:13.750 --> 01:14:14.951
It's just a souvenir.

01:14:14.984 --> 01:14:16.219
It's Luisa's.

01:14:16.252 --> 01:14:17.521
You stole it.

01:14:17.554 --> 01:14:19.055
Please, she gave it to me.

01:14:19.088 --> 01:14:20.790
Not that it's any
business of yours.
Now, as I said.

01:14:20.824 --> 01:14:21.825
(GRUNTS)

01:14:23.693 --> 01:14:24.828
(GROANS)

01:14:26.763 --> 01:14:28.698
All right. Move it out.

01:14:40.243 --> 01:14:41.545
El Gallo.

01:14:53.723 --> 01:14:54.958
El Gallo!

01:14:59.863 --> 01:15:01.097
El Gallo?

01:15:02.599 --> 01:15:03.833
El Gallo!

01:15:12.108 --> 01:15:13.176
(SOBBING)

01:15:20.249 --> 01:15:24.654
EL GALLO:
There is a curious paradox
that no one can explain.

01:15:24.688 --> 01:15:28.758
Who understands the secret
of the reaping of the grain.

01:15:28.792 --> 01:15:33.196
Who understands
why spring is born
out of winter's laboring pain.

01:15:33.229 --> 01:15:36.633
Or why we all must die a bit
before we grow again.

01:15:41.971 --> 01:15:43.106
Matt.

01:15:47.176 --> 01:15:48.778
What happened?

01:15:49.913 --> 01:15:51.915
You look awful.

01:15:51.948 --> 01:15:54.784
It isn't worth tears,
Luisa, please.

01:15:58.855 --> 01:16:01.925
Did you find the money
and the beautiful women.

01:16:02.726 --> 01:16:04.761
I can't remember, I...

01:16:04.794 --> 01:16:07.664
I was drugged
or hypnotized
or something.

01:16:09.799 --> 01:16:12.802
There was this
funny light and mirrors.

01:16:13.369 --> 01:16:14.771
I know.

01:16:15.404 --> 01:16:17.306
And there was this music.

01:16:17.340 --> 01:16:19.909
Strange music and people

01:16:19.943 --> 01:16:21.778
Turning and spinning and...

01:16:21.811 --> 01:16:23.112
Wearing masks.

01:16:24.047 --> 01:16:25.782
I remember crying out.

01:16:25.815 --> 01:16:27.350
But no one came
to help you.

01:16:34.023 --> 01:16:35.158
I'm sorry, Matt.

01:16:37.093 --> 01:16:38.795
No, I...

01:16:38.828 --> 01:16:40.263
It's all right.

01:16:42.131 --> 01:16:44.067
I deserved it.

01:16:44.100 --> 01:16:45.835
I've been foolish.

01:16:46.870 --> 01:16:48.237
I have, too.

01:16:49.305 --> 01:16:51.374
Believe me,
more than you.

01:16:56.746 --> 01:17:00.149
* When the moon was young

01:17:00.183 --> 01:17:04.020
* When the month was May

01:17:04.053 --> 01:17:10.259
* When the stage was hung
for my holiday

01:17:11.094 --> 01:17:14.698
* I saw shining lights

01:17:14.731 --> 01:17:18.201
* But I never knew

01:17:18.234 --> 01:17:21.137
* They were you
They were you

01:17:22.138 --> 01:17:23.940
* They were you

